Convert months into a usual format for graphing

In [6]:
year = 1999
months = np.empty(len(df['Month']), dtype='datetime64[M]')
for x in range(len(df['Month'])):
    if x % 12 == 0:
        year += 1
    if x % 12 >= 9:
        month = str(x % 12 + 1)
    else:
        month = '0' + str(x % 12 + 1)
    
    date = str(year) + '-' + month
    months[x] = np.datetime64(date)

Get mean and median of all fuel maxima

In [9]:
def meanAndMedian(x):
    meanMedianRaw = []

    for i in range(len(x)):
        interPeakDistance = 0
        medianPeakDistance = 0
        interPeakDistance = (x[i][0] + x[i][-1]) / len(x[i])
        peakDiff = np.empty(len(x[i]) - 1, dtype = int)
    
        for j in range(len(x[i]) - 1):
            peakDiff[j] = x[i][j + 1] - x[i][j]
    
        peakDiff.sort()
        lenPeakDiff = int(len(peakDiff) / 2)
        if len(peakDiff) % 2 == 0:
            medianPeakDistance = (peakDiff[lenPeakDiff] + peakDiff[lenPeakDiff - 1]) / 2
        else:
            medianPeakDistance = peakDiff[lenPeakDiff]

        meanMedianRaw.append([fuels[i], interPeakDistance, medianPeakDistance])

    meanMedianProcessed = \
        pd.DataFrame(np.asarray(meanMedianRaw), columns = ['fuel', 'mean (months)', 'median (months)'])
    
    return meanMedianProcessed

So we see that spikes happen an avg of every 5 months for all the fuel types. This is different from what someone might initially expect: once every 3 months perhaps, to rise and fall with each quarter.
